The '''Office of Alcohol and Tobacco Control''' is a [[Louisiana]] [[state government]] agency that regulates the [[alcoholic beverage]] and [[tobacco]] industries. The Office places emphasis on combating underage purchasing and drinking of alcohol and tobacco.

The current Commissioner of the Office of Alcohol and Tobacco Control is [[Troy Hebert]] who was appointed on 24 November 2010.<ref name=hebert>{{cite web| url = http://www.weeklycitizen.com/breaking/x1384138406/State-Sen-Hebert-named-ATC-Commissioner | title = State Sen. Hebert named ATC Commissioner | accessdate = 2010-11-25 | date = 2010-11-24 | publisher = ''[[The Gonzales Weekly Citizen]]''}}</ref>

